  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "PBZICdXaBFA6ebsvRMoZwVJuMto=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "When a user opens Connect on a new device or after clearing browser data, recovery proceeds from wallet-only state:\n\n1. User connects MetaMask.\n2. Plugin requests `personal_sign`, which re-derives the SAME Swarm key as before.\n3. `SwarmChannel.pollInbox()` reads the user manifest from feed `ph:v2:user:<address>`.\n4. For each drive listed, read the drive manifest at `ph:v2:drive:<driveId>`.\n5. For each document not present locally: read its manifest at `ph:v2:doc:<docId>`, download each operation batch from `/bytes` (auto-decrypted), create SyncOperations, and enqueue in the inbox.\n6. SyncManager applies via `reactor.load()` using the ORIGINAL document IDs, so links and cross-doc references survive.\n7. The cursor advances in `sync_cursors`, the drive materializes in PGlite with correct folder structure, and future polls are incremental.\n\nKey properties: cursor-based so nothing re-downloads; no race conditions because SyncManager processes inbox before outbox, preventing re-upload of just-recovered ops; failed operations flow to `sync_dead_letters` for retry.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
    }
  },
